				\begin{document}$$N_{{{\text{gv}}}} = \frac{{\Delta \rho g k_{{{\text{av}}}} }}{{v_{x} \mu_{{{\text{nw}}}} }}\frac{\Delta x}{{\Delta z}}$$\end{document}where ux is the total flow velocity in the horizontal (x) direction, ∆x and ∆z are the system dimensions, μnw is the viscosity of the non-wetting phase (hydrogen), kav is the average permeability, ∆ρ is fluid density difference, g is the acceleration due to gravity and (dPc/dSw) is the capillary pressure gradient as a function of wetting-phase saturation.

